Usage: create_parasitic_coordinate_transform [-help] { -inst <string> [-x_offset <float>] [-y_offset <float>] [-orient {R0 R90 R180 R270 MY MX90 MX MY90}] [-x_block_origin <float>] [-y_block_origin <float>] [-relative_to_parent ]} | { -reset  }

-help                       # Prints out the command usage
-inst <string>              # instance name (string, required)
-orient {R0 R90 R180 R270 MY MX90 MX MY90}
                            # instance orientation valid options (enum, required)
-relative_to_parent         # Instance transformation is provided with respect
                            # to immediate parent (bool, required)
-reset                      # reset spef transform (bool, required)
-x_block_origin <float>     # In case of non-origin block, offset x coordinate
                            # in microns (float, optional)
-x_offset <float>           # instance x coordinate in microns
                            # (float, required)
-y_block_origin <float>     # In case of non-origin block, offset y coordinate
                            # in microns (float, optional)
-y_offset <float>           # instance y coordinate in microns
                            # (float, required)